  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nAdding solc options in truffle configuration `truffle.js`, does not trigger a recompile of contracts upon `truffle migrate`.\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. compile project\r\n2. update `truffle.js` to toggle solc optimization\r\n3. notice truffle migrate migrates contracts compiled in `1.`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nJust as when you edit a solidity file, the contract is recompiled upon `truffle migrate`, I expected the change in solc parameters to trigger recompilation of the project upon `truffle migrate`.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Debian GNU/Linux 9\r\n* Truffle version: 4.0.1\r\n* Ethereum client: testrpc 6.0.1\r\n* node version: 8.9.0\r\n* npm version: 5.5.1\r\n",
